<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OXNARD; 
</P>
<P>
PHONE SOLICITOR WARNING ISSUED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WEINSTOCK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A top Oxnard school official has warned residents to beware of unauthorized 
telephone solicitations for contributions to pay for schoolbooks. 
</P>
<P>
Norman Brekke, superintendent of the Oxnard Elementary School District, asked 
for a police investigation of the unauthorized solicitations. 
</P>
<P>
The pitch involves a request to contribute money to help buy coloring books for 
elementary school students, made in the name of a group called Californians 
Against Drugs, Brekke said. 
</P>
<P>
Representatives of the group could not be reached for comment. 
</P>
<P>
In fact, the district has not endorsed the project, Brekke said. 
</P>
<P>
"It appears that there is some considerable pressure to get these 
contributions," Brekke said. "A courier would come to the home within the hour 
to pick up the donation." 
</P>
<P>
The solicitations came to light when a number of residents called the district. 
Brekke had no information on how many contributors are involved. CAROL 
WEINSTOCK 
</P>
</TEXT>
