<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men were in critical condition after their car crashed Thursday into a 
power pole in the 1300 block of Kelton Road, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The men, whose names were not available but who are believed to be in their 
20s, were taken unconscious to UC San Diego Medical Center and Mercy Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
The car was "wrapped around (the) power pole and completely severed at the fire 
wall," a Fire Department spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
There was no fire and no one else was injured. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses told police the car was speeding when the driver lost control and 
slammed into the pole about 3:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The crash occurred across the street from Johnson Elementary School, but school 
had already finished for the day. 
</P>
<P>
David Smith, an San Diego Gas &amp; Electric spokesman, said the accident cut 
power to about 100 customers for a few hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
