<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: CARLSBAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Carlsbad Unified School District board of trustees has agreed to pay a 
suspended teacher's aide $10,000 in exchange for his immediate resignation, a 
district official said. 
</P>
<P>
Gregory Tirona also gave up all legal claims he might have against the 
district, including wages, benefits and future employment rights. 
</P>
<P>
Tirona was accused of selling steroids to three students in late 1988. His 
trial ended last month with the jury hung 11-1 for acquittal. He will not be 
tried again. 
</P>
<P>
"It's a closed case right now," said Gerald Tarman, the school district's 
personnel director. "There's agreement on both sides." 
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Tirona on Monday and was subject to the board's 
approval Wednesday at a closed hearing. 
</P>
<P>
Two weeks ago, the board fired Tirona after a 30-day suspension. Wednesday's 
agreement frees the district from possible lawsuits by Tirona. 
</P>
</TEXT>
