<P>
Bones found scattered in thick brush at the end of Big Rock Road in Santee may 
be those of a retired Navy man who disappeared in 1987. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy Coroner Robert Grubb said the human bones were found last week and that 
an initial examination by a forensic anthropologist has determined they 
belonged to an elderly male. He said investigators believe they may be the 
remains of Abe Pikelny, a retired Navy chief petty officer who went out for a 
walk on Sept. 25, 1987, and never returned home. Pikelny lived in a mobile home 
park on Mission Gorge Road with his sister about a mile from where the bones 
were found. 
