<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHARGERS-MIAMI 1982 OVERTIME GAME IS CHOSEN BEST OF '80S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ORLANDO, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chargers' 41-38 overtime victory over Miami in a 1982 playoff was selected 
as the top NFL game of the 1980s by a panel of Hall of Fame voters. 
</P>
<P>
The game, played in the Orange Bowl, featured Miami's comeback from a 24-0 
deficit before the Chargers won on Rolf Benirschke's 29-yard field goal 13:52 
into overtime. 
</P>
<P>
Second in the voting was the 1989 Super Bowl in which San Francisco beat 
Cincinnati 20-16 on Joe Montana' 10-yard touchdown pass to John Taylor with 34 
seconds left. The scoring pass came at the end of a 92-yard, 11-play drive. 
</P>
<P>
Another Montana drive was the feature of the third-best game, San Francisco's 
28-27 victory over Dallas in the 1981 NFC title game. It featured "The Catch" 
-- Dwight Clark's leaping six-yard TD grab at the end of the 89-yard drive. 
</P>
<P>
The rest of the top 10: 
</P>
<P>
4. Denver 23, Cleveland 20 in overtime in the 1986 AFC title game. 
</P>
<P>
5. Denver 38, Cleveland 33 in the 1987 AFC title game. 
</P>
<P>
6. Dallas 31, Washington 30, Sept. 5, 1983. 
</P>
<P>
7. Miami 38, Chicago 24, Dec. 2, 1985. 
</P>
<P>
8. Oakland 14, Cleveland 12, 1980 AFC playoff, Jan. 4, 1981. 
</P>
<P>
9. San Francisco 38, New Orleans 35, Dec. 7, 1980. 
</P>
<P>
10. Chicago 20, Philadelphia 12, 1988 playoff, Dec. 31, 1988, a game in which 
the second half was obscured by fog. 
</P>
</TEXT>
