<HEADLINE>
<P>
CS LONG BEACH, ARIZONA STATE PLAY IN NIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DICK WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TEMPE, Ariz. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Long Beach (22-8), which figured to be playing in the NCAA 
tournament, plays Arizona State (15-15) in a first-round National Invitation 
Tournament game here tonight at 6 p.m. (PST). 
</P>
<P>
This is the 49ers' second NIT appearance in the last three seasons. 
</P>
<P>
CS Long Beach had won nine consecutive games until it lost to Nevada Las Vegas, 
92-74, Sunday in the final of the Big West tournament. The 49ers learned at 
halftime that they needed to beat UNLV to gain an NCAA tournament berth. 
</P>
<P>
Freshman guard Lucious Harris, who scored 75 points in the Big West tournament, 
leads the 49ers with a 14-point average. 
</P>
