<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kline Apologizes to Stutterers: Kevin Kline apologized to the National 
Stuttering Project this week for offending stutterers with his Oscar-winning 
role in "A Fish Called Wanda" about a year after he was asked to make a 
statement. 
</P>
<P>
"I apologize for the pain I might have inadvertently caused persons who 
stutter. The character I portrayed in 'A Fish Called Wanda' should not be 
considered a role model for any civilized person when talking to a stutterer," 
Kline wrote in a letter to the group. Kline has resisted an apology because he 
said the organization missed the humor in his role. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
