<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Best of Broadcast News: News coverage of the San Francisco earthquake and 
Hurricane Hugo earned top honors Thursday in the 50th annual Peabody Awards, 
called the Pulitzer Prize of broadcast journalism. The University of Georgia, 
which governs the awards, cited KCBS-AM radio and KGO-TV, both in San 
Francisco, for coverage of the earthquake and WCSC-TV in Charleston, S.C., for 
reporting on Hurricane Hugo. Other recipients included CBS Radio News in New 
York and Cable News Network in Atlanta for coverage of last spring's uprising 
in China. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
