<TEXT>
<P>
Sendero Luminoso (Shining Path) guerrillas shot and killed 19 peasants, nearly 
all of them women and children, in a small Andean hamlet where they had fled to 
escape rebel attacks in their own village, police said. The massacre occurred 
in Pishupiaco, 60 miles southeast of Huancayo, a major trading center in the 
Andes 120 miles east of the capital city of Lima. Reports of the killings were 
delayed by the village's isolation. 
