<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
CAMARILLO; 
</P>
<P>
VOTE PAVES WAY FOR LAND DEVELOPMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Camarillo City Council approved creation of a tax district and sale of up 
to $31 million in bonds to pay for road and sewer improvements, taking a step 
toward major development on vacant land in the west end of the Ventura County 
city. The council voted 4 to 0 to form the district near Camarillo Airport, 
clearing the way for developments that city officials have already approved on 
about 600 acres. It was Camarillo's largest planned borrowing for improvements 
since 1987, when the entire city treasury of $25 million was lost in high-risk 
trading ventures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
