<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 3; Column 4; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
56 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The heart problem that led to pitcher Dave Leiper's overnight stay in a 
hospital early this week is one doctors believe can be corrected with 
"relatively minor surgery," Oakland Athletic General Manager Sandy Alderson 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Leiper has what is described as an irregular heartbeat. He suffered a mild 
heart attack two years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
