<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
OHIO; 
</P>
<P>
BUZZARD WATCHERS SATED IN HINCKLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With more than 170 years of tradition under their wings, the buzzards returned 
as scheduled to Hinckley, Ohio, delighting buzzard watchers from across the 
country who had been waiting since before dawn. According to local folklore, 
the buzzards, or turkey vultures, have returned to this small northeastern Ohio 
town yearly on March 15 since 1819, when frozen carcasses from a Christmas Eve 
community hunt began defrosting. About 150 people, including a dozen wearing 
buzzard costumes, awaited the large black scavengers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
