<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLOCAUST MEMORIAL DEFACED IN W. BERLIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WEST BERLIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vandals stuck a pig's head with a swastika in its mouth on a memorial in West 
Berlin to Jews deported and exterminated by Adolf Hitler's Nazi regime, police 
said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
It was the second time in two years that the monument has been defaced. In 
January 1989, a group calling itself the "April 20 movement" -- the date of 
Hitler's birthday -- claimed responsibility for an identical attack. 
</P>
<P>
World Jewish groups have expressed concern at the rise of neo-Nazism among 
young people in both East and West Germany. 
</P>
