<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
KOVIC ENDORSES YUDELSON IN RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vietnam veteran Ron Kovic may have decided not to run against Rep. Robert K. 
Dornan (R-Garden Grove), but he has not disappeared from the Orange County 
political scene. 
</P>
<P>
Jerry Yudelson, one of two Democratic candidates for the 72nd Assembly District 
seat held by Curt Pringle (R-Garden Grove), announced Thursday that he has the 
endorsement of Kovic, whose life is portrayed in the movie "Born on the Fourth 
of July." 
</P>
<P>
Kovic could not be reached for comment Thursday, but in a statement released by 
Yudelson's Assembly campaign office, Kovic says that Yudelson has his "full 
support and endorsement." 
</P>
<P>
Yudelson said he is "pleased to receive the endorsement of a remarkable man." 
</P>
<P>
Yudelson's Democratic opponent in the June primary is Tom Umberg, a former 
federal prosecutor who lives in Garden Grove. Umberg said that he had not 
sought Kovic's endorsement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
