</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AT&amp;T May Broaden Early Retirement Plan: American Telephone &amp; Telegraph, 
continuing its campaign to cut costs, said that it is talking to its two major 
unions about an early-retirement program that for the first time would be 
offered to non-management employees. Interest in a new early-retirement plan 
aimed at non-management levels surfaced last year, a spokesman said, after 
about 12,500 managers -- 37% of those eligible accepted the incentive package. 
Stinson did not disclose how many of the company's 165,000 non-management 
employees might be affected nor when an early-retirement plan might be offered. 
</P>
