<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOT, HIP &amp; HAPPENING: HIGH LIFE A WEEKLY FORUM FOR HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Coaches from seven Saddleback Valley high schools will challenge members of the 
Rams in a basketball game on March 23 at El Toro High School to raise funds for 
Saddleback Community Enterprises for the Developmentally Disabled. 
</P>
<P>
Among the Rams scheduled to play are Jim Everett, Mike Lansford, Duval Love, 
Kevin Greene, Mike Piel, Flipper Anderson, LeRoy Irvin, Mike Wilcher, Aaron Cox 
and Robert Delpino. 
</P>
<P>
Coaches from Capistrano Valley, El Toro, Laguna Hills, Mission Viejo, Santa 
Margarita, Silverado and Trabuco Hills will participate, as will each high 
school's cheerleaders on the sidelines. 
</P>
<P>
Doors open at 7 p.m. and both Rams players and Rams cheerleaders will be 
available for autographs and pictures before the game and during halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets, which are $10 for adults and $7 for students and children, are 
available through participating schools and at the Saddleback Community 
Enterprises office, 25701 Taladro Circle, Mission Viejo, or by calling (714) 
837-7280. 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback Community Enterprises is a sheltered workshop for developmentally 
disabled adults. It serves the handicapped by providing vocational training and 
employment opportunities. 
</P>
<P>
"Honesty is the best image." -- Ziggy (Tom Wilson) 
</P>
</TEXT>
