1 HELD AFTER 3 BANKS ROBBED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Banks in Garden Grove, La Palma and Fullerton were robbed Thursday, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
In the Garden Grove robbery, a bank employee chased a bandit and held him until 
officers arrived. 
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred about 2:15 p.m. when the robber entered First Interstate 
Bank in the 12000 block of Valley View Street. After presenting a note 
demanding money, the bandit left with an undisclosed amount of cash, Lt. Ron 
Weigand said. 
</P>
<P>
Weigand said a bank employee followed the man and detained him until officers 
arrived. All the money was recovered, Weigand said. Police later booked David 
Anderson, 38, on suspicion of bank robbery. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities are searching for suspects who held up banks in La Palma and 
Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
In the La Palma robbery, a man wearing dark sunglasses presented a note 
demanding money to a teller at the Sumitomo Bank in the 5000 block of 
Orangethorpe Avenue, a police spokeswoman said. The man escaped with an 
undisclosed amount of money, she said. 
</P>
<P>
A similar incident occurred at 1:37 p.m. at the Sanwa Bank in the 3000 block of 
East Yorba Linda Boulevard in Fullerton, where a bandit escaped with an 
undisclosed amount of cash. 
</P>
<P>
Police said they do not believe that the incidents are related. 
