<P>
PPG SELLS SHARE OF GERMAN FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PITTSBURGH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PPG Industries has sold its 75% interest in West German equipment maker 
Lenhardt Maschinenbau GmbH, the company said today. 
</P>
<P>
The buyer is Bystronic Maschinen AG of Butzberg, Switzerland. The purchase 
price was not given. General Manager Karl Lenhardt holds the remaining shares 
in the company. 
</P>
<P>
Lenhardt, based in Neuhausen-Hamberg, makes equipment used to produce 
insulating glass units and other fabricated glass products. Bystronic produces 
equipment for the glass, metals, plastics and agriculture industries. 
</P>
<P>
PPG said it sold its interest because the fabricating equipment business no 
longer is appropriate to its long-term strategic objectives. PPG is one of the 
world's leading producers of flat and fabricated glass. 
</P>
</TEXT>
