<P>
PAINTING CAN'T LEAVE FRANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Van Gogh watercolor expected to fetch $5 million when it is sold by its 
French owners next week must not leave the country, the Culture Ministry has 
ruled. 
</P>
<P>
A ministry statement declared the canvas "Roofs" was of national historical 
interest. 
</P>
<P>
"Roofs," showing rooftops and the countryside surrounding the Dutch city of The 
Hague, was completed in 1882, eight years before Van Gogh committed suicide in 
France. 
</P>
<P>
It is part of a collection belonging to the family of French businessman 
Georges Renand and comes up for auction Tuesday at the Drouot auction house. 
</P>
