</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLOTHES AND CASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Clipboard researched by Elena Brunet, Dallas M. Jackson and Janice L. Jones 
/ Los Angeles Times; Graphics by Doris Shields / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Costa Mesa is king when it comes to money and clothes in Orange County. In the 
first quarter of 1989 (the most recent period from which information is 
available), Costa Mesa had the highest taxable sales of clothing and shoes, the 
largest per capita and per store sales and the biggest percentage of all sales 
in the county. Its first quarter, 1989, sales increase over first quarter, 
1988, was topped only by the 185% increase in La Habra. 
</P>
<P>
the comparable period of 1988 and 39% more than 1987. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
